			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Xoce, the cost in the 10-19 spells comes mostly from having to BUY the Quils and Papers from other crafters.
<br />

<br />
Im one of the sinners that scribed the recipe books outside my class when it was possible. (Btw, there was a HUGE market for selling the level 10 recipe books for a while, people would buy them for 4s and sell them for 14s by the dozen.)
<br />

<br />
Anyway, if we werent PAYING to BETA test this game then Id feel some small morsel of guilt, but since I get to deal with all the fun bugs, I feel theres balance here.
<br />

<br />
If they made it so ALL the components in the recipe had an effect on the outcome or in the overall increase/decrease that went with each tick, then it wouldnt matter so much, because its pretty tough to make Pristine Quils and Papers with no Tier 2 craftsman skills.
<br />

<br />
If they had made the books NOT scribeable by other classes, it wouldnt be an issue either.
<br />

<br />
If they had FIXED societies when the game went live then people could buy those items off the merchants in the tradeskill instances. (Although you CAN buy those now on some tradeskill instances.. its only the Wholesalers tradeskill instances where you could get the quest to harvest 15 badger pelts, then turn RIGHT around and buy those 15 badger pelts off the broker for around 8s total and turn BACK around and get your quest reward of 12s while leveling your guild. You could do this as fast as you could turn, spin and buy.
<br />

<br />
People leveled their societies this way, and if you want YOUR society to be able to sell this crap, then LEAVE your hometown and go join the societies that already did that. Because they forked up the tradeskill societies so bad that only one or two in a city (Freeport or Qeynos) actually have people in them. The rest have minimal people and are hurting because you cant buy the tradeskill components for Tier 2.
<br />

<br />
Tradeskills (Some advanced books that drop dont even HAVE recipes on them, and potions are forked up as well.) are severely lacking in the testing and refinement process.
<br />

<br />
Societies werent thought out well enough.
<br />

<br />
The number of sub combines is a little on the extreme side.
<br />

<br />
Interdependency is a little overboard as well. (To make LEATHER GLOVES requires 8 different tradeskill classes to make something for you.)
<br />

<br />
With all that said, I still love the game. I just wish they had tested a little more before releasing.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
